<promed@promedmail.org>
[There were many documented cases of humans transmitting _Mycobacterium
tuberculosis_ to dairy cows before the United States tuberculosis control
campaign made significant gains in the first half of last century (ah, I
never tire of the new decade, century, millennium novelty). So it may not
surprise anyone if an analogous phenomenon occurs in captive elephants,
particularly if they have close contact with their keepers. It would be
interesting to know if the type of housing or environment was a risk factor
for transmission. - Mod.PC
